[metadata]
Name:Enduring Ideal — Epic cast lock + repeating upkeep search
Goal:Survive
Turns:10
Difficulty:Medium
Description:Enduring Ideal (5WW): search your library for an enchantment, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle. Epic — for the rest of the game you can't cast spells; at the beginning of each of your upkeeps, copy this spell except for its epic ability. Setup: P0 has Enduring Ideal in hand with exactly 7 mana available (5 Plains + Island tapped for {5}{W}{W}). Library contains Ghostly Prison, Honden of Cleansing Fire, Solitary Confinement. On turn 2 (MAIN1) P0 casts Enduring Ideal: the first enchantment (Ghostly Prison) should enter the battlefield; P0's cant_cast_spells flag should be set; a repeating upkeep delayed trigger should be registered. On turn 3 (Upkeep) the Epic trigger fires: the second enchantment (Honden of Cleansing Fire) enters the battlefield. Turn 4 upkeep: Solitary Confinement enters. Three aspects under test: (1) initial search puts enchantment on battlefield, (2) Epic cast-lock blocks future spell casting, (3) repeating upkeep trigger fires each subsequent upkeep.

